{"type":"text","text":"same memory as this buffer, only bound to type "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"T"},{"type":"text","text":". The buffer"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"parameter contains a number of complete instances of "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"T"},{"type":"text","text":" based"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"on the capacity of the original buffer and the stride of "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Element"},{"type":"text","text":"."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"The closure’s buffer argument is valid only for the duration of the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"closure’s execution. If "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"body"},{"type":"text","text":" has a return value, that value"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"is also used as the return value for the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"withMemoryRebound(to:_:)"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"method."}],"type":"paragraph"}]}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Return Value","anchor":"return-value"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The return value, if any, of the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"body"},{"type":"text","text":" closure parameter."}]}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"type":"heading","text":"Discussion","level":2,"anchor":"discussion"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Use this method when you have a buffer of memory bound to one type and"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"you need to access that memory as a buffer of another type. Accessing"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"memory as type ","type":"text"},{"code":"T","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" requires that the memory be bound to that type. A","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"memory location may only be bound to one type at a time, so accessing","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"the same memory as an unrelated type without first rebinding the memory","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"is undefined.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The number of instances of ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"T"},{"text":" referenced by the rebound buffer may be","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"different than the number of instances of ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Element"},{"text":" referenced by the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"original buffer. The number of instances of ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"T"},{"text":" will be calculated","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"at runtime.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Any instance of "},{"code":"T","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" within the re-bound region may be initialized or"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"uninitialized. Every instance of "},{"code":"Pointee","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" overlapping with a given"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"instance of "},{"code":"T","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" should have the same initialization state (i.e."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"initialized or uninitialized.) Accessing a ","type":"text"},{"code":"T","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" whose underlying","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"code":"Pointee","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" storage is in a mixed initialization state shall be","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"undefined behaviour.","type":"text"}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Because this buffer’s memory is no longer bound to its "},{"code":"Element","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" type"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"while the "},{"code":"body","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" closure executes, do not access memory using the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"original buffer from within "},{"code":"body","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":". Instead, use the "},{"code":"body","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" closure’s"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"buffer argument to access the values in memory as instances of type"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"code":"T","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"After executing "},{"code":"body","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":", this method rebinds memory back to the original"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"code":"Element","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" type."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"style":"note","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Only use this method to rebind the buffer’s memory to a type"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"that is layout compatible with the currently bound "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Element"},{"type":"text","text":" type."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"The stride of the temporary type ("},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"T"},{"type":"text","text":") may be an integer multiple"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"or a whole fraction of "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Element"},{"type":"text","text":"‘s stride."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"To bind a region of memory to a type that does not match these"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"requirements, convert the buffer to a raw buffer and use the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"raw buffer’s "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"withMemoryRebound(to:)"},{"type":"text","text":" method."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"If "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"T"},{"text":" and ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Element"},{"type":"text","text":" have different alignments, this buffer’s"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"code":"baseAddress","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" must be aligned with the larger of the two alignments.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"type":"aside","name":"Note"}]}],"identifier":{"url":"doc://com.apple.Swift/documentation/Swift/UnsafeBufferPointer/withMemoryRebound(to:_:)","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"sections":[],"kind":"symbol","metadata":{"role":"symbol","externalID":"s:SRsRi_zrlE17withMemoryRebound2to_qd_1_qd__m_qd_1_SRyqd__Gqd_0_YKXEtqd_0_YKs5ErrorRd_0_Ri_d__Ri_d_1_r1_lF","symbolKind":"method","extendedModule":"Swift","roleHeading":"Instance Method","modules":[{"name":"Swift"}],"title":"withMemoryRebound(to:_:)","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"withMemoryRebound"},{"kind":"text","text":"<"},{"kind":"genericParameter","text":"T"},{"kind":"text","text":", "},{"kind":"genericParameter","text":"E"},{"kind":"text","text":", "},{"kind":"genericParameter","text":"Result"},{"kind":"text","text":">("},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"to"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"T","preciseIdentifier":"s:SRsRi_zrlE17withMemoryRebound2to_qd_1_qd__m_qd_1_SRyqd__Gqd_0_YKXEtqd_0_YKs5ErrorRd_0_Ri_d__Ri_d_1_r1_lF1TL_qd__mfp"},{"kind":"text","text":".Type, ("},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"_"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"internalParam","text":"buffer"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"UnsafeBufferPointer","preciseIdentifier":"s:SR"},{"kind":"text","text":"<"},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"T","preciseIdentifier":"s:SRsRi_zrlE17withMemoryRebound2to_qd_1_qd__m_qd_1_SRyqd__Gqd_0_YKXEtqd_0_YKs5ErrorRd_0_Ri_d__Ri_d_1_r1_lF1TL_qd__mfp"},{"kind":"text","text":">) "},{"kind":"keyword","text":"throws"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"E","preciseIdentifier":"s:SRsRi_zrlE17withMemoryRebound2to_qd_1_qd__m_qd_1_SRyqd__Gqd_0_YKXEtqd_0_YKs5ErrorRd_0_Ri_d__Ri_d_1_r1_lF1EL_qd_0_mfp"},{"kind":"text","text":") -> "